Description: The National Institute of Labour Studies (NILS) is an autonomous research institute within the Faculty of Social and Behavioural Sciences at Flinders University, and is Australias oldest dedicated labour market research centre. NILS specialises in research and consulting in the fields of work and labour markets, and is renowned for combining rigorous analysis with a continuing concern for the wellbeing of people as workers.
